1
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:43,440
♪I don't want to hear you
nagging nonstop♪

2
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:46,790
♪Can't you just give me the result♪

3
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:49,960
♪Don't think being older
makes you so much greater♪

4
00:00:50,170 --> 00:00:51,710
♪Just bring it on♪

5
00:00:51,910 --> 00:00:53,170
♪Watch how I'll handle you♪

6
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,080
♪Hey, I'll just keep on nagging♪

7
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,010
♪Keep on nagging♪

8
00:00:59,010 --> 00:01:02,030
♪You're annoying; do not get me mad♪

9
00:01:02,030 --> 00:01:05,140
♪I'm always the one
taking the blame for you♪

10
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:08,690
♪Don't be afraid to speak;
I might hold a grudge♪

11
00:01:08,690 --> 00:01:09,970
♪No. 132♪

12
00:01:09,970 --> 00:01:10,910
♪357, what do you want♪

13
00:01:11,110 --> 00:01:12,280
♪Stop right there♪

14
00:01:13,540 --> 00:01:16,900
♪In this noisy, rowdy world,
fate is so amazing♪

15
00:01:17,060 --> 00:01:20,150
♪When we go crazy together,
joy is always with us♪

16
00:01:20,150 --> 00:01:23,260
♪We'll party till dawn♪

17
00:01:23,260 --> 00:01:26,540
♪Laughing, jumping, with no worries♪

18
00:01:26,540 --> 00:01:28,060
♪You're clearly so strange♪

19
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:29,580
♪I'm clearly so cute♪

20
00:01:29,580 --> 00:01:32,630
♪Even if they don't get it,
it doesn't matter♪

21
00:01:32,630 --> 00:01:36,330
♪Even if it's always crazy and weird♪

22
00:01:36,330 --> 00:01:39,410
♪I still need fresh reasons for myself♪

23
00:01:42,590 --> 00:01:47,070
=Hilarious Family 2=

24
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:50,260
=Episode 20=

25
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:53,300
(Careful Pastry)

26
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:54,800
Sir, come in, please.

27
00:02:02,830 --> 00:02:04,370
Presentable, indeed.

28
00:02:06,860 --> 00:02:08,560
Today, don't fight Xiaoyu again.

29
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:10,020
I had a hard time calming her down.

30
00:02:10,020 --> 00:02:11,450
Don't worry. We won't fight.

31
00:02:11,830 --> 00:02:12,770
This is nice, too.

32
00:02:14,140 --> 00:02:15,280
I have some good news.

33
00:02:17,620 --> 00:02:18,950
How could you have good news?

34
00:02:18,950 --> 00:02:20,460
Tell me. What's the good news?

35
00:02:20,460 --> 00:02:21,400
Sit down.

36
00:02:23,790 --> 00:02:25,240
I've got us some extra money.

37
00:02:27,390 --> 00:02:28,330
Two hundred taels.

38
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:30,730
Two hundred?

39
00:02:31,420 --> 00:02:32,800
You can always count on me, huh?

40
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:35,000
The two of you make a plan

41
00:02:35,460 --> 00:02:36,610
for how you'll use the money.

42
00:02:36,830 --> 00:02:38,240
Then you give me ten percent each.

43
00:02:38,580 --> 00:02:40,170
The account will be clear.

44
00:02:41,990 --> 00:02:42,930
No.

45
00:02:43,790 --> 00:02:44,730
No?

46
00:02:46,670 --> 00:02:48,280
Are you not clear yet?

47
00:02:49,180 --> 00:02:51,120
200 taels.

48
00:02:51,460 --> 00:02:53,090
Are you not clear yet?

49
00:02:53,420 --> 00:02:54,520
I said, no.

50
00:02:55,350 --> 00:02:56,550
If we give you more shares,

51
00:02:56,550 --> 00:02:57,890
we'll be working for you.

52
00:02:59,860 --> 00:03:00,800
Now, you should

53
00:03:00,990 --> 00:03:02,110
think about this shop,

54
00:03:02,110 --> 00:03:03,070
right?

55
00:03:03,070 --> 00:03:04,170
With the extra money,

56
00:03:04,860 --> 00:03:06,120
we can do a lot more things,

57
00:03:06,390 --> 00:03:07,520
hire a lot more helpers,

58
00:03:07,670 --> 00:03:09,450
and make more pastries.

59
00:03:09,860 --> 00:03:11,270
Just twenty percent.

60
00:03:11,270 --> 00:03:12,860
Be more far-sighted.

61
00:03:12,860 --> 00:03:13,960
You should be far-sighted.

62
00:03:13,970 --> 00:03:14,860
Yeah.

63
00:03:14,860 --> 00:03:16,450
How about you give us twenty percent?

64
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:17,650
Lin Donglin,

65
00:03:17,650 --> 00:03:18,950
are you also being ungrateful?

66
00:03:18,950 --> 00:03:20,610
Let me confirm one thing.

67
00:03:21,580 --> 00:03:22,680
My family doesn't know, huh?

68
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:26,860
No.

69
00:03:26,860 --> 00:03:28,090
Then how did you get the money?

70
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:30,700
None of your business.

71
00:03:30,700 --> 00:03:32,020
I know

72
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:32,960
many rich young guys.

73
00:03:33,740 --> 00:03:34,680
Impressive.

74
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:35,960
Anyway, I will not

75
00:03:36,110 --> 00:03:37,050
give you my share.

76
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:44,140
And you?

77
00:03:44,140 --> 00:03:45,170
I'm on Xiaoyu's side.

78
00:03:45,990 --> 00:03:47,400
Sometimes, too much money

79
00:03:48,180 --> 00:03:49,120
will cause trouble.

80
00:03:50,180 --> 00:03:51,120
What?

81
00:03:51,230 --> 00:03:52,170
You two...

82
00:03:54,660 --> 00:03:55,700
(Careful Pastry)

83
00:03:55,700 --> 00:03:56,890
You rejected extra money.

84
00:03:57,020 --> 00:03:57,960
You won't prosper!

85
00:04:15,850 --> 00:04:16,740
I told you,

86
00:04:16,740 --> 00:04:18,470
the new pastry wasn't good.

87
00:04:18,470 --> 00:04:20,060
- Shh.
- Xiaoyu didn't listen.

88
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:21,030
Stop. Lower your voice.

89
00:04:21,030 --> 00:04:21,970
Stop!

90
00:04:33,550 --> 00:04:34,490
Dear.

91
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:35,800
What a coincidence.

92
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:37,800
Where have you been?

93
00:04:38,350 --> 00:04:39,650
I was buying pastries for you.

94
00:04:41,470 --> 00:04:45,960
The two of you together?

95
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:49,860
We met at the door.

96
00:04:49,860 --> 00:04:50,800
Yes.

97
00:04:51,820 --> 00:04:52,760
Nonsense!

98
00:04:53,820 --> 00:04:55,260
I saw you come out

99
00:04:55,260 --> 00:04:56,570
of Careful Pastry.

100
00:04:58,990 --> 00:05:00,280
I didn't make it clear.

101
00:05:01,180 --> 00:05:02,350
We met at the door

102
00:05:02,350 --> 00:05:03,300
- of that shop.
- Yes.

103
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:04,380
So, we came back together.

104
00:05:04,380 --> 00:05:05,320
That's right.

105
00:05:05,940 --> 00:05:06,910
What were you there for?

106
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:08,160
- Pastries.
- Where are they?

107
00:05:09,710 --> 00:05:10,720
I ate them in the shop.

108
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:12,890
You were pretty quick.

109
00:05:13,620 --> 00:05:14,550
Fine.

110
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:16,330
Forget about the pastry thing.

111
00:05:17,030 --> 00:05:18,210
So, tell me.

112
00:05:20,110 --> 00:05:21,840
Yesterday morning,

113
00:05:22,150 --> 00:05:24,300
why did you two go together

114
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:25,240
to buy some flour?

115
00:05:25,420 --> 00:05:26,400
Flour...

116
00:05:26,790 --> 00:05:28,090
Why did I buy flour?

117
00:05:28,230 --> 00:05:29,210
I proposed to go.

118
00:05:29,420 --> 00:05:30,360
Me.

119
00:05:31,710 --> 00:05:33,570
It was me

120
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:36,010
who should go with Jiao'e.

121
00:05:36,350 --> 00:05:38,600
But we couldn't carry it.

122
00:05:39,230 --> 00:05:41,150
So, Mr. Lin offered to help us.

123
00:05:41,150 --> 00:05:43,770
Yes. It was too heavy to be carried.

124
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:45,450
Who sent you?

125
00:05:46,790 --> 00:05:47,730
Me.

126
00:05:49,910 --> 00:05:50,850
It was me.

127
00:05:51,790 --> 00:05:53,810
Yesterday, I wanted some pancakes.

128
00:05:53,940 --> 00:05:55,160
There wasn't enough flour.

129
00:05:55,380 --> 00:05:56,810
So, I sent Mingzhen to buy some.

130
00:05:57,030 --> 00:05:57,970
Right, Mingzhen?

131
00:05:58,420 --> 00:05:59,360
Yes.

132
00:06:03,620 --> 00:06:04,560
Fine.

133
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:06,570
I'll say no more

134
00:06:07,790 --> 00:06:09,250
about the flour thing.

135
00:06:11,420 --> 00:06:13,280
But you're Ms. Luo's maid.

136
00:06:13,990 --> 00:06:16,280
How dare you send Grandmother's maid?

137
00:06:18,670 --> 00:06:20,090
What's wrong with that?

138
00:06:20,710 --> 00:06:21,990
I don't even mind.

139
00:06:21,990 --> 00:06:23,330
Why do you bother?

140
00:06:23,990 --> 00:06:24,930
No more questions.

141
00:06:25,150 --> 00:06:26,090
Dismissed.

142
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:28,410
Grandmother!

143
00:06:30,910 --> 00:06:33,250
Dear, it's just a misunderstanding.

144
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:34,710
- It is?
- I'll put

145
00:06:34,710 --> 00:06:35,770
the pastries back.

146
00:06:35,910 --> 00:06:36,860
Go ahead.

147
00:06:36,860 --> 00:06:37,890
I'll go back to work.

148
00:06:38,350 --> 00:06:39,740
Look at the mess.

149
00:06:39,740 --> 00:06:40,680
Stop!

150
00:06:42,620 --> 00:06:44,480
Even if it all makes sense,

151
00:06:45,940 --> 00:06:47,090
then why

152
00:06:48,030 --> 00:06:50,130
have you always been unseen?

153
00:06:51,030 --> 00:06:51,910
You've also been gone

154
00:06:51,910 --> 00:06:53,330
at the same time.

155
00:06:53,550 --> 00:06:55,600
Why do you often come and go together?

156
00:06:55,740 --> 00:06:56,680
Confess!

157
00:06:57,110 --> 00:06:58,300
What's your relationship

158
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,920
with that pastry shop?

159
00:07:01,110 --> 00:07:02,050
It's me.

160
00:07:04,060 --> 00:07:05,520
I sent them there.

161
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:06,970
Mother?

162
00:07:07,790 --> 00:07:08,790
Why?

163
00:07:08,790 --> 00:07:10,210
Why did you send them?

164
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:11,500
Because I want Jiao'e

165
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:13,010
to buy some for your grandmother.

166
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:15,620
Thank you, Muyun,

167
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:16,600
for thinking about me.

168
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:19,010
Jiao'e can eat them in the shop.

169
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,120
Why?

170
00:07:27,860 --> 00:07:28,800
It's...

171
00:07:28,940 --> 00:07:29,880
Why do you...?

172
00:07:29,990 --> 00:07:30,930
You...

173
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:32,570
Why do you all take his side?

174
00:07:32,790 --> 00:07:33,820
No, no.

175
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:35,040
We don't want you to misunderstand.

176
00:07:35,180 --> 00:07:37,260
Right. You're a great girl,

177
00:07:37,260 --> 00:07:38,520
but you're just suspicious.

178
00:07:39,820 --> 00:07:40,760
Don't laugh.

179
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:44,280
I'm thinking too much?

180
00:07:44,550 --> 00:07:45,810
Yes, you are.

181
00:07:47,790 --> 00:07:48,730
You really are.

182
00:07:57,110 --> 00:07:58,920
I knew about the shop thing.

183
00:07:59,350 --> 00:08:00,330
And I helped you out.

184
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:02,360
Give me twenty percent.

185
00:08:08,260 --> 00:08:09,720
Come on.

186
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,460
(Intoxicating Spring)

187
00:08:13,030 --> 00:08:14,450
What did Ms. Xue say?

188
00:08:15,150 --> 00:08:16,890
She asked me for twenty percent.

189
00:08:19,180 --> 00:08:20,120
Another twenty percent.

190
00:08:20,380 --> 00:08:21,360
Now I understand.

191
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:24,520
All my family members know it now.

192
00:08:25,470 --> 00:08:27,570
Even the maids know it.

193
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,620
But I...

194
00:08:30,620 --> 00:08:32,110
Because I borrowed money

195
00:08:32,110 --> 00:08:33,050
from the maids.

196
00:08:33,230 --> 00:08:35,310
What is your problem, Lyu Jiao'e?

197
00:08:35,310 --> 00:08:36,690
Every day, I work diligently

198
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:37,590
and sneak all the time,

199
00:08:37,590 --> 00:08:39,230
just to avoid them.

200
00:08:39,230 --> 00:08:40,240
But you...

201
00:08:40,950 --> 00:08:41,890
Think like this.

202
00:08:42,470 --> 00:08:43,590
Just because they knew,

203
00:08:43,590 --> 00:08:45,860
they kept your secret
from Zhenzhu, right?

204
00:08:45,860 --> 00:08:47,380
Or it would have been revealed.

205
00:08:47,380 --> 00:08:48,230
You silly man.

206
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:49,170
What secret?

207
00:08:57,780 --> 00:08:59,290
Zhenzhu.

208
00:09:00,580 --> 00:09:03,020
(Jinyu Tea)

209
00:09:06,740 --> 00:09:07,680
Chief Luo,

210
00:09:08,230 --> 00:09:09,590
why did you let Jing Kan take part

211
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:10,880
as Old Lady requested?

212
00:09:11,990 --> 00:09:13,620
Each tea shop

213
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:15,450
can offer two kinds of tea
for the contest.

214
00:09:16,310 --> 00:09:18,240
But giving him one quota

215
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:20,210
is still unfair to us.

216
00:09:20,860 --> 00:09:23,000
Whether he takes part,

217
00:09:23,470 --> 00:09:25,210
I will win the first prize

218
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:27,760
of the Tea Contest.

219
00:09:29,430 --> 00:09:30,370
Mr. Lu.

220
00:09:30,860 --> 00:09:31,800
Let's do this.

221
00:09:32,350 --> 00:09:34,070
Stop what you're doing

222
00:09:34,070 --> 00:09:35,020
right now.

223
00:09:35,020 --> 00:09:35,960
Take some gifts

224
00:09:36,190 --> 00:09:37,360
and go to Wuyi Mountain

225
00:09:37,780 --> 00:09:39,330
to invite Mr. Huang over.

226
00:09:39,660 --> 00:09:40,600
Mr. Huang?

227
00:09:41,230 --> 00:09:42,190
You mean the disciple

228
00:09:42,190 --> 00:09:43,760
of Monk Da Fang?

229
00:09:45,430 --> 00:09:47,240
He'll help us to pan-fire the tea.

230
00:09:47,740 --> 00:09:48,680
With him,

231
00:09:49,110 --> 00:09:52,360
we'll have a half chance

232
00:09:53,020 --> 00:09:54,570
to win this year's contest.

233
00:09:55,110 --> 00:09:57,000
As for the other half...

234
00:09:57,710 --> 00:09:58,650
Mr. Ren.

235
00:09:59,620 --> 00:10:01,000
You go to the Capital.

236
00:10:01,310 --> 00:10:02,620
Whatever it takes,

237
00:10:02,620 --> 00:10:04,540
invite Tea Master over

238
00:10:04,540 --> 00:10:06,960
to assist us in making the tea leaves

239
00:10:07,310 --> 00:10:08,960
for the Tea Contest.

240
00:10:09,350 --> 00:10:10,880
It's not easy to invite them.

241
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:12,140
Otherwise,

242
00:10:12,140 --> 00:10:14,050
I wouldn't send you.

243
00:10:14,740 --> 00:10:15,680
That's right.

244
00:10:16,660 --> 00:10:18,480
If they can come,

245
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:20,640
we will be certain

246
00:10:21,070 --> 00:10:22,810
to win the Tea Contest.

247
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:24,130
So,

248
00:10:24,310 --> 00:10:25,810
you must invite them over

249
00:10:26,260 --> 00:10:28,290
at whatever cost.

250
00:10:32,230 --> 00:10:33,230
Chief Luo,

251
00:10:33,230 --> 00:10:34,230
it's late.

252
00:10:34,230 --> 00:10:35,170
You get some rest.

253
00:10:35,310 --> 00:10:36,450
I'll take my leave

254
00:10:36,620 --> 00:10:37,720
with the two of them.

255
00:10:40,710 --> 00:10:41,650
This way, please.

256
00:10:43,110 --> 00:10:44,050
I'm so tired.

257
00:10:49,590 --> 00:10:51,960
Give this letter to Wan'er

258
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:54,240
and ask her to instruct Aji.

259
00:10:54,620 --> 00:10:56,810
Tell her to persuade Aji to study hard.

260
00:10:57,110 --> 00:10:58,140
Even given a chance,

261
00:10:58,140 --> 00:11:00,090
he still has to be capable enough.

262
00:11:00,430 --> 00:11:01,370
Madam,

263
00:11:01,590 --> 00:11:03,110
if you want Young Master Aji

264
00:11:03,110 --> 00:11:04,050
to go into business,

265
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:06,120
why don't you instruct him?

266
00:11:07,110 --> 00:11:08,050
We...

267
00:11:09,070 --> 00:11:10,010
Go on.

268
00:11:11,110 --> 00:11:12,880
Do you expect more gossip?

269
00:11:13,590 --> 00:11:14,530
Use your brain.

270
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,640
What is Auntie thinking of?

271
00:11:25,950 --> 00:11:27,050
Why must I go into business?

272
00:11:27,380 --> 00:11:28,260
Like I said,

273
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:29,640
I'm in no mood for this.

274
00:11:30,590 --> 00:11:32,290
It's the family inheritance.

275
00:11:32,370 --> 00:11:33,260
Young Master Aji,

276
00:11:33,260 --> 00:11:34,290
you are the nephew

277
00:11:34,590 --> 00:11:35,530
of Madam.

278
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:37,720
You must be interested in business.

279
00:11:37,860 --> 00:11:39,900
You just haven't realized it yet.

280
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:41,240
Let me be frank with you.

281
00:11:42,140 --> 00:11:44,120
- I won't do that.
- No, Young Master Aji.

282
00:11:44,590 --> 00:11:45,470
Madam has a plan

283
00:11:45,470 --> 00:11:47,210
for your future.

284
00:11:47,350 --> 00:11:48,480
Just do what you're told.

285
00:11:48,620 --> 00:11:49,960
She won't hurt you.

286
00:11:50,190 --> 00:11:51,860
Will you just stop?

287
00:11:51,860 --> 00:11:53,470
I mean what I say.

288
00:11:53,470 --> 00:11:54,720
Don't push it.

289
00:11:55,780 --> 00:11:56,840
Madam also said,

290
00:11:56,990 --> 00:11:58,070
every time you come here,

291
00:11:58,070 --> 00:11:59,450
you'll get ten taels.

292
00:12:01,020 --> 00:12:01,960
Deal.

293
00:12:02,710 --> 00:12:03,650
Give me the money.

294
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,430
You haven't seen Ms. Zhu yet.

295
00:12:05,430 --> 00:12:06,540
It doesn't count.

296
00:12:06,540 --> 00:12:08,070
So, I have to see her, right?

297
00:12:08,070 --> 00:12:09,010
Of course.

298
00:12:09,470 --> 00:12:11,290
Alright. Ms. Zhu.

299
00:12:12,540 --> 00:12:14,140
- Keep your voice down.
- Ms. Zhu!

300
00:12:14,140 --> 00:12:15,380
Don't disturb her business.

301
00:12:15,380 --> 00:12:16,760
Ms. Zhu. Ms. Zhu.

302
00:12:17,140 --> 00:12:18,120
See? She isn't in.

303
00:12:18,620 --> 00:12:19,560
I should go.

304
00:12:21,540 --> 00:12:22,480
Give me the money.

305
00:12:23,540 --> 00:12:25,480
Not until you learn, according to Madam.

306
00:12:25,990 --> 00:12:27,950
You're setting one trap after another.

307
00:12:27,950 --> 00:12:29,050
So, this is Aji, huh?

308
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:36,420
(Zhu Wan'er, Owner of Fu's Restaurant)

309
00:12:37,830 --> 00:12:38,770
Ms. Zhu.

310
00:12:41,110 --> 00:12:42,050
Young Master Aji,

311
00:12:42,230 --> 00:12:43,480
this is Ms. Zhu,

312
00:12:43,780 --> 00:12:44,810
owner of this restaurant.

313
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:52,960
Say hello.

314
00:12:54,430 --> 00:12:55,370
Hello, Ms. Zhou.

315
00:12:56,990 --> 00:12:58,570
I'm Ms. Zhu.

316
00:13:00,860 --> 00:13:02,540
He doesn't have a knack

317
00:13:02,540 --> 00:13:03,720
for business yet.

318
00:13:04,260 --> 00:13:06,600
Please be more patient with him.

319
00:13:09,540 --> 00:13:11,290
Stop nagging, will you?

320
00:13:17,140 --> 00:13:18,600
You have half an hour.

321
00:13:19,380 --> 00:13:20,640
If you sell this pot of wine,

322
00:13:20,860 --> 00:13:21,800
I'll instruct you.

323
00:13:31,020 --> 00:13:31,960
I'll buy it.

324
00:13:33,660 --> 00:13:35,000
You think you're smart?

325
00:13:37,020 --> 00:13:38,600
In business, you need real skills

326
00:13:38,710 --> 00:13:39,930
instead of petty tricks.

327
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:41,470
Stop using

328
00:13:41,470 --> 00:13:42,690
such childish tricks.

329
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:46,930
He might be too young

330
00:13:47,070 --> 00:13:48,170
to understand this.

331
00:13:48,590 --> 00:13:49,810
I have things to do today.

332
00:13:50,260 --> 00:13:51,410
You may leave now.

333
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:54,960
Don't go, Ms. Zhu.

334
00:13:55,590 --> 00:13:56,530
Ms. Zhu.

335
00:14:01,070 --> 00:14:02,010
Young Master Aji,

336
00:14:02,350 --> 00:14:03,960
I think you just used

337
00:14:04,660 --> 00:14:05,600
a very smart trick.

338
00:14:07,830 --> 00:14:08,770
You don't tell me.

339
00:14:10,310 --> 00:14:11,690
Wait for me. Umbrella.

340
00:14:27,310 --> 00:14:28,930
Dear, have a pork knuckle.

341
00:14:30,020 --> 00:14:31,450
No, thanks.

342
00:14:34,760 --> 00:14:36,170
Shall I get you some soup?

343
00:14:36,350 --> 00:14:37,330
No, Mother.

344
00:14:37,660 --> 00:14:39,090
I don't really want that.

345
00:14:47,660 --> 00:14:48,600
Dear,

346
00:14:49,260 --> 00:14:50,530
are you really not mad

347
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:52,690
at the pastry shop thing?

348
00:14:52,830 --> 00:14:54,360
Why do I have to be mad?

349
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:57,090
I didn't mean to hide it from you.

350
00:14:57,260 --> 00:14:59,470
Yeah. I don't mean to lie, either.

351
00:14:59,470 --> 00:15:00,760
It's fine.

352
00:15:00,990 --> 00:15:02,350
Everybody else knew it.

353
00:15:02,350 --> 00:15:03,230
I'm the only one

354
00:15:03,230 --> 00:15:04,330
who wasn't aware.

355
00:15:04,620 --> 00:15:06,690
I don't care. No big deal.

356
00:15:07,620 --> 00:15:08,690
I knew it.

357
00:15:08,950 --> 00:15:10,140
All of you

358
00:15:10,140 --> 00:15:12,210
would discard me one day.

359
00:15:12,470 --> 00:15:13,620
This day just came earlier

360
00:15:13,620 --> 00:15:15,450
than I ever imagined.

361
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:18,700
Kid, don't think like that.

362
00:15:18,710 --> 00:15:19,620
Yeah.

363
00:15:19,620 --> 00:15:21,590
- We wouldn't discard you.
- Yeah.

364
00:15:21,590 --> 00:15:23,020
You're the spine of our family.

365
00:15:23,020 --> 00:15:23,880
That's right.

366
00:15:23,890 --> 00:15:25,480
Drop the act, will you?

367
00:15:26,350 --> 00:15:27,780
I always know

368
00:15:27,780 --> 00:15:28,720
what you think of me.

369
00:15:28,860 --> 00:15:30,240
In your eyes, actually.

370
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:32,720
I've always been inferior.

371
00:15:33,230 --> 00:15:34,480
No, no, no.

372
00:15:34,620 --> 00:15:35,640
That's not true.

373
00:15:35,780 --> 00:15:37,190
You may still deny it,

374
00:15:37,190 --> 00:15:38,930
but I will not.

375
00:15:39,660 --> 00:15:41,930
Everyone is born alone

376
00:15:42,230 --> 00:15:43,690
and will die alone.

377
00:15:44,070 --> 00:15:45,410
So, I think

378
00:15:46,470 --> 00:15:47,960
we'll just live our own lives.

379
00:15:49,470 --> 00:15:50,410
Don't bother.

380
00:15:51,710 --> 00:15:52,930
I'm not worth it.

381
00:15:53,660 --> 00:15:55,240
Dear. Dear.

382
00:15:55,950 --> 00:15:58,170
Oh, she's never been like this before.

383
00:15:58,740 --> 00:16:00,330
It's... It's really abnormal.

384
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:01,710
She didn't even scold me.

385
00:16:01,710 --> 00:16:02,990
Will she get upset

386
00:16:02,990 --> 00:16:03,830
and hurt herself?

387
00:16:03,830 --> 00:16:04,740
I'll go check on her.

388
00:16:04,740 --> 00:16:06,780
Wait. You may make her angrier.

389
00:16:06,780 --> 00:16:07,720
I'll go.

390
00:16:08,140 --> 00:16:09,110
Mother, calm her down.

391
00:16:09,110 --> 00:16:10,050
I will.

392
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:25,290
Oh, look.

393
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:27,760
You're wearing lipstick.

394
00:16:28,380 --> 00:16:29,320
You look gorgeous.

395
00:16:30,190 --> 00:16:33,110
Right. Makeup can make you happy.

396
00:16:33,110 --> 00:16:34,050
I'm going out.

397
00:16:35,310 --> 00:16:36,410
Where are you going?

398
00:16:36,830 --> 00:16:38,760
To find a way out.

399
00:16:39,470 --> 00:16:40,930
You have your own businesses.

400
00:16:41,260 --> 00:16:42,480
Who can I rely on?

401
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:44,210
I have to rely on myself.

402
00:16:45,310 --> 00:16:46,190
Come on.

403
00:16:46,190 --> 00:16:48,210
Don't blame Donglin.

404
00:16:48,540 --> 00:16:50,860
He had wanted to tell you.

405
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:52,660
But he didn't want you to despise

406
00:16:52,660 --> 00:16:53,930
that small business.

407
00:16:55,430 --> 00:16:56,350
But anyway,

408
00:16:56,350 --> 00:16:58,310
I've verified it.

409
00:16:58,310 --> 00:16:59,950
His pastry shop

410
00:16:59,950 --> 00:17:01,350
has good business.

411
00:17:01,350 --> 00:17:03,140
It'll only do

412
00:17:03,140 --> 00:17:06,360
our family good.

413
00:17:10,190 --> 00:17:12,060
Mother, have you ever noticed?

414
00:17:12,060 --> 00:17:13,150
Every time you start

415
00:17:13,150 --> 00:17:14,870
to make an empty promise,

416
00:17:14,870 --> 00:17:16,680
you'll keep saying "our family".

417
00:17:16,950 --> 00:17:18,400
You think I can't see through you?

418
00:17:18,630 --> 00:17:20,400
When have I made empty promises?

419
00:17:21,950 --> 00:17:22,890
Zhenzhu,

420
00:17:23,020 --> 00:17:24,060
you're the only one

421
00:17:24,060 --> 00:17:25,580
in this world

422
00:17:25,580 --> 00:17:27,050
that I can rely on.

423
00:17:27,390 --> 00:17:29,540
I certainly have plans for you.

424
00:17:29,540 --> 00:17:31,050
We're a family, after all.

425
00:17:34,060 --> 00:17:35,010
Family?

426
00:17:37,740 --> 00:17:39,580
Family is what has hurt me most

427
00:17:39,580 --> 00:17:40,680
in my life.

428
00:17:41,430 --> 00:17:42,840
Sometimes, I wish I had no family.

429
00:17:43,150 --> 00:17:44,430
Because this word

430
00:17:44,430 --> 00:17:46,490
is actually a burden to me.

431
00:17:47,230 --> 00:17:48,250
And I understand.

432
00:17:48,540 --> 00:17:50,870
I'm also your burden.

433
00:17:50,870 --> 00:17:51,780
No, no.

434
00:17:51,780 --> 00:17:53,840
Don't think like that, kid.

435
00:17:56,470 --> 00:17:57,600
I'll skip Grandfather.

436
00:17:58,470 --> 00:18:00,160
He despised me when he was alive.

437
00:18:01,260 --> 00:18:02,200
And Grandmother.

438
00:18:03,430 --> 00:18:05,010
She always thinks

439
00:18:05,260 --> 00:18:07,530
her grandson is better than I am.

440
00:18:09,340 --> 00:18:10,290
Family?

441
00:18:10,990 --> 00:18:12,120
I've seen through it.

442
00:18:15,150 --> 00:18:16,120
Are you done talking?

443
00:18:16,870 --> 00:18:18,530
If you don't mind,
I'll go make a living.

444
00:18:18,910 --> 00:18:19,850
Zhenzhu.

445
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:24,020
You...

446
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:25,970
You want a shop, right?

447
00:18:27,870 --> 00:18:28,810
Fine.

448
00:18:28,950 --> 00:18:30,810
You'll have Wushen Temple Shop.

449
00:18:32,340 --> 00:18:34,290
I'll make you the manager.

450
00:18:35,150 --> 00:18:37,150
You said we all had a business, right?

451
00:18:37,150 --> 00:18:39,710
I'll give you this shop,

452
00:18:39,710 --> 00:18:40,670
so you won't say this

453
00:18:40,670 --> 00:18:42,600
to break my heart.

454
00:18:46,820 --> 00:18:48,330
Are you really willing?

455
00:18:48,780 --> 00:18:50,530
I have to, anyway.

456
00:18:53,230 --> 00:18:55,290
Zhenzhu, listen to me.

457
00:18:55,470 --> 00:18:56,780
Sometimes, you may not understand

458
00:18:56,780 --> 00:18:58,050
what I'm doing.

459
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:00,430
But I swear to you.

460
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:01,500
I sincerely want you

461
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,050
to live the best life.

462
00:19:03,260 --> 00:19:04,330
In this world,

463
00:19:04,630 --> 00:19:06,290
if I didn't care about you,

464
00:19:06,540 --> 00:19:07,810
who else would I care about?

465
00:19:08,820 --> 00:19:09,740
Fine.

466
00:19:09,740 --> 00:19:10,810
Then now,

467
00:19:10,990 --> 00:19:12,430
you go to the shop

468
00:19:12,430 --> 00:19:13,880
and announce this seriously.

469
00:19:16,950 --> 00:19:17,890
Come on.

470
00:19:18,230 --> 00:19:20,490
Zhenzhu, what have I done to you?

471
00:19:20,710 --> 00:19:22,250
Why do you not trust me at all?

472
00:19:30,180 --> 00:19:34,300
(Jinyu Tea Plantation)

473
00:19:36,470 --> 00:19:37,920
I have something to announce.

474
00:19:38,190 --> 00:19:39,260
From this day on,

475
00:19:39,260 --> 00:19:40,120
Zhenzhu will be

476
00:19:40,130 --> 00:19:42,050
the chief manager of this shop.

477
00:19:42,740 --> 00:19:43,840
Are you clear?

478
00:19:44,740 --> 00:19:45,770
Are you?

479
00:19:47,470 --> 00:19:48,810
Then say hello.

480
00:19:49,390 --> 00:19:51,090
Hello, Ms. Jing.

481
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:52,250
Call her Chief.

482
00:19:53,430 --> 00:19:54,810
Yes, Chief Jing.

483
00:19:58,740 --> 00:19:59,740
Let me say something.

484
00:19:59,740 --> 00:20:01,160
Sorry to interrupt you.

485
00:20:01,910 --> 00:20:03,840
There's another thing.

486
00:20:04,470 --> 00:20:06,050
Mr. Jia has left, right?

487
00:20:07,150 --> 00:20:08,230
Liu, Ma,

488
00:20:08,230 --> 00:20:09,330
She, and Chu.

489
00:20:09,740 --> 00:20:11,340
I'll make the four of you

490
00:20:11,340 --> 00:20:13,570
managers of this shop.

491
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:16,200
Managers?

492
00:20:16,470 --> 00:20:17,410
Managers.

493
00:20:18,020 --> 00:20:18,960
Say it.

494
00:20:19,150 --> 00:20:20,090
Four of us?

495
00:20:20,540 --> 00:20:21,480
Yes.

496
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:23,260
I'm telling you,

497
00:20:23,260 --> 00:20:25,260
the four of you must help Zhenzhu

498
00:20:25,260 --> 00:20:26,770
to manage this shop.

499
00:20:26,950 --> 00:20:28,440
Never can you slack off, understand?

500
00:20:28,450 --> 00:20:29,300
Alright.

501
00:20:29,300 --> 00:20:30,240
Wait, Mother.

502
00:20:30,820 --> 00:20:33,090
I never said I needed assistance.

503
00:20:33,710 --> 00:20:35,390
As a newcomer,

504
00:20:35,390 --> 00:20:36,260
you aren't familiar.

505
00:20:36,260 --> 00:20:37,880
You certainly need assistance.

506
00:20:38,190 --> 00:20:39,200
No, no, no.

507
00:20:39,340 --> 00:20:41,580
The moment you announced

508
00:20:41,580 --> 00:20:42,990
that I became

509
00:20:42,990 --> 00:20:44,400
the manager,

510
00:20:44,670 --> 00:20:45,580
I should be in charge

511
00:20:45,580 --> 00:20:46,950
of all personnel arrangements

512
00:20:46,950 --> 00:20:48,390
in this shop.

513
00:20:48,390 --> 00:20:51,230
You shouldn't interfere. Understand?

514
00:20:51,230 --> 00:20:52,250
No, no, no.

515
00:20:52,430 --> 00:20:54,870
I'm not interfering, all right?

516
00:20:54,870 --> 00:20:57,010
You either give me this shop,

517
00:20:57,340 --> 00:20:59,250
or even if you hesitate,

518
00:20:59,430 --> 00:21:01,050
you don't need to do this.

519
00:21:01,390 --> 00:21:03,120
It's not what you think.

520
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:07,920
What the heck.

521
00:21:09,190 --> 00:21:10,160
Fine, fine.

522
00:21:10,820 --> 00:21:11,760
I won't interfere.

523
00:21:14,060 --> 00:21:15,590
- Do you promise?
- Yes.

524
00:21:15,630 --> 00:21:17,680
You really won't?

525
00:21:18,540 --> 00:21:19,880
Hope you'll keep your promise.

526
00:21:21,820 --> 00:21:22,760
Go back to work.

527
00:21:23,100 --> 00:21:24,440
I should say that!

528
00:21:24,780 --> 00:21:25,720
Go ahead, then.

529
00:21:27,580 --> 00:21:28,770
I don't want to say anything.

530
00:21:31,390 --> 00:21:32,530
Go back to work.

531
00:21:41,150 --> 00:21:42,330
This is ridiculous.

532
00:21:51,470 --> 00:21:52,970
How are you doing the accounts?

533
00:21:53,260 --> 00:21:54,490
Five taels are missing.

534
00:21:54,740 --> 00:21:55,970
Why did you shout?

535
00:21:58,500 --> 00:21:59,490
I'll just give it to you.

536
00:22:23,340 --> 00:22:24,280
Stop playing.

537
00:22:25,300 --> 00:22:26,440
I'm not playing.

538
00:22:26,580 --> 00:22:27,520
I'm doing the accounts.

539
00:22:29,260 --> 00:22:30,200
Accounts?

540
00:22:35,950 --> 00:22:38,580
There are rules for the abacus.

541
00:22:38,580 --> 00:22:39,530
How can you calculate

542
00:22:40,670 --> 00:22:41,880
when you don't even know that?

543
00:22:44,430 --> 00:22:45,340
Wan'er,

544
00:22:45,340 --> 00:22:47,400
were you drunk last night?

545
00:22:47,540 --> 00:22:49,330
I made you yam and wolfberry porridge.

546
00:22:49,580 --> 00:22:50,680
It's on your table.

547
00:22:58,710 --> 00:23:00,250
I don't mean to be opportunistic.

548
00:23:01,260 --> 00:23:03,050
I'm just caring about you.

549
00:23:06,340 --> 00:23:07,280
Luo Aji,

550
00:23:07,820 --> 00:23:09,730
if you really want
to care about someone,

551
00:23:10,310 --> 00:23:11,780
you should first get to know

552
00:23:11,780 --> 00:23:13,530
what she actually wants.

553
00:23:14,150 --> 00:23:15,600
Don't call me Luo Aji.

554
00:23:15,950 --> 00:23:16,970
Just call me Aji.

555
00:23:18,060 --> 00:23:19,360
I'm not kidding.

556
00:23:20,910 --> 00:23:21,910
Then, can you stop

557
00:23:21,910 --> 00:23:23,440
treating me like a kid?

558
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:28,930
I'm not treating you like a kid.

559
00:23:29,430 --> 00:23:30,790
But look at what you've done.

560
00:23:31,130 --> 00:23:31,990
I just can't take you

561
00:23:31,990 --> 00:23:33,570
for an adult.

562
00:23:33,780 --> 00:23:34,960
Go back and tell your auntie.

563
00:23:35,130 --> 00:23:36,150
You don't need to come.

564
00:23:36,910 --> 00:23:37,810
Yuanbao.

565
00:23:39,300 --> 00:23:40,240
See him out.

566
00:23:40,670 --> 00:23:41,610
Alright.

567
00:23:42,260 --> 00:23:44,010
Wan...

568
00:23:45,100 --> 00:23:46,040
Wan'er.

569
00:23:56,670 --> 00:23:57,610
Aji.

570
00:23:58,910 --> 00:23:59,850
Aji.

571
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:01,240
What's wrong with you?

572
00:24:01,580 --> 00:24:02,520
What happened?

573
00:24:03,630 --> 00:24:04,500
Nothing.

574
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:06,740
Then, why are you drinking alone?

575
00:24:06,740 --> 00:24:07,680
Today,

576
00:24:10,580 --> 00:24:11,970
I said something wrong, I guess.

577
00:24:13,950 --> 00:24:15,730
What did you say?

578
00:24:16,150 --> 00:24:17,440
I asked Wan'er

579
00:24:17,990 --> 00:24:19,640
not to call me Luo Aji,

580
00:24:20,340 --> 00:24:21,530
but Aji.

581
00:24:23,740 --> 00:24:24,920
Then, she was mad.

582
00:24:27,950 --> 00:24:29,400
For this?

583
00:24:31,260 --> 00:24:32,400
I don't think

584
00:24:33,260 --> 00:24:35,970
Wan'er gets mad that easily.

585
00:24:37,580 --> 00:24:38,520
Oh, I see.

586
00:24:39,150 --> 00:24:41,490
She wanted to teach you something.

